# Requests for the NATS example (example/nats/main.go).
#
# 1. docker compose -f example/nats/compose.yaml up -d
# 2. go run ./example/nats
# 3. send the requests below (JetBrains / VS Code REST Client).
#
# Flow: POST /publish (CE type http.command.nats) -> HTTP mux publishes the
# result to NATS -> NATS mux consumes it and logs "Received event from NATS".

@host = http://localhost:8080

### Happy path — binary-mode CloudEvent, routed to NATS then logged.
POST {{host}}/publish
Ce-Id: 11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111
Ce-Source: demo/test.http
Ce-Specversion: 1.0
Ce-Type: http.command.nats
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ada",
  "age": 36
}

### Validation failure — "age" is required (validate preflight rejects it).
POST {{host}}/publish
Ce-Id: 22222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222
Ce-Source: demo/test.http
Ce-Specversion: 1.0
Ce-Type: http.command.nats
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "grace"
}

### No matching route — unknown type (http mux has ReportOnNoMatch: true).
POST {{host}}/publish
Ce-Id: 33333333-3333-3333-3333-333333333333
Ce-Source: demo/test.http
Ce-Specversion: 1.0
Ce-Type: http.command.unknown
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "alan",
  "age": 41
}

### Structured-mode CloudEvent — full envelope in the body.
POST {{host}}/publish
Content-Type: application/cloudevents+json

{
  "id": "44444444-4444-4444-4444-444444444444",
  "source": "demo/test.http",
  "specversion": "1.0",
  "type": "http.command.nats",
  "datacontenttype": "application/json",
  "data": {
    "name": "linus",
    "age": 29
  }
}
